reviews.review_text: Very nice Well recorded and an excellent show as well. There are some brief AUD patches but they aren't terribly intrusive or annoying. The show features some excellent playing by Jerry and the band. Superb versions of Bird Song, Lazy Lightning/Supplication (one of the best I've heard btw) and an excellent Scarlett/Fire and Lost Sailor/Saint, the jam coming out of Saint and high energy renditions of the songs at the end of the second set make this a must hear show.

Great show and video Is only a small portion of this AWESOME show but still get to see what I saw so many years before. Doubt I was even in view of the stage cause I know surely boogied my ass off all night at this show.
http://youtu.be/KYdfjj_fFEY
Great Wharf Rat As usual, another version of Wharf Rat that I listened to 3 times in a row before proceeding to the end.  Nice concert altogether as usual.

good somewhat different sounding SBD the SBD's from the 1st half of the year generally lack bass, etc

from May on the SBD's are better, more fatter bass, better mixes etc

this show has a tad bit of 'echo' added to the vocals which adds ambiance so the vocals arent too hot etc works well for tenn jed lazy lightnin, scarlet and really the whole show.
i must have hit my head not sure why i gave this 4 stars, it's truly one of the finest 1st sets of the Brent era, if not *the* finest.
Been turnin on the the Brent years Solid sounding recording of a pretty fun set. Shoulda been there.
